article.headline: Wright and Valek outscore Iowa 43-41 before resting
article.linkText: Wright, Valek outscore Iowa as No. 12 Purdue rolls
article.story:
INDIANAPOLIS (AP) -- Shereka Wright matched her season-high with
28 points and Erika Valek had 15 as No. 12 Purdue reached the Big
Ten tournament championship game for the sixth time with an 84-57
victory Sunday against Iowa.

	   The third-seeded Boilermakers (25-5) will play fourth-seed Ohio
State in the title game Monday. The Buckeyes advanced with a
72-61 victory over top seed Penn State.

	   Purdue won three consecutive tournaments from 1998-2000 and lost
the 1996 and 2001 title games.

	   Johanna Solverson led Iowa (16-14) with 16 points and Jenny
Lillis added 12. Kristi Faulkner, who scored 46 points in the
tournament's first two games, was held to eight on 3-for-10
shooting.

	   Valek and Wright, both juniors from Texas, have carried Purdue
all year and Sunday was no exception. They combined to shoot
15-for-30 from the floor and Wright was 12-for-14 from the free-throw line as the Boilermakers beat the Hawkeyes for the third time
this season.

	   Purdue lost in the tournament semifinals a year ago to
lightly-regarded Indiana. The Boilermakers said they would not make
the same mistake of underestimating seventh-seeded Iowa, which had
already knocked off Minnesota.

	   Purdue still missed seven consecutive shots and 11 of 12 in one
stretch and trailed 31-28 after a 3-pointer by Faulkner.

	   Then Purdue's Beth Jones hit a 3-pointer to spark a 16-1 run.
Mary Jo Noon's jumper as time expired capped the spurt and gave
Purdue a 44-32 halftime lead.

	   Iowa committed seven of its 22 turnovers during the run.

	   Wright did what she does best during the half -- slashing her way
to the basket and drawing fouls. She scored 18 points in the half
thanks to a 10-for-12 effort from the line. Eight of the free
throws came during Purdue's run.

	   With about nine minutes left in the game, Wright and Valek had
outscored Iowa 43-41. The two were went to the bench shortly after.
